title: Forcing a passage of the Hudson River, 9 October 1776
description: HMS Phoenix, Roebuck and Tartar, accompanied by three smaller vessels, forcing their way through a cheval-de-frise on the Hudson River with the Forts Washington and Lee and several batteries on both sides. The painting is a copy by Thomas Mitchell after the original rendering of the subject, a scene from the American Revolutionary War, by Dominic Serres the Elder.

title: The Course of Empire: The Consummation of Empire
The Castello Plan
description: The Castello Plan shows the Dutch colonial city of New Amsterdam in 1660. It includes details of the city's layout, the position of the fort, and the location of the church and the city wall.

title: Pop Shop IV
description: This print includes one of his most well-known symbols: the barking dog. Haring would feature the same dog symbol in many of his works

title: Campbell's Soup Cans
description: When he first exhibited Campbell’s Soup Cans in 1962, the canvases were displayed together on shelves, like products in a grocery aisle.

title: Cow Wallpaper
description: Reproduction of Warhol's Cow wallpaper, which was originally created in 1966. The wallpaper features a repeating pattern of cows, and is a playful take on the idea of wallpaper as a decorative element.

title: Le Rêve
description: Yadwiga, ancienne amie polonaise de Rousseau, allongée, écoutant, en pleine jungle, la flûte d'un charmeur

title: The Great Wave off Kanagawa
description: the first in his series Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji, in which the use of Prussian blue revolutionized Japanese prints
